        <h2>Communications Expert Witness for Patent Litigation</h2>

        <p>A seasoned <a href="/">telecommunications expert witness</a> and <a href="/communications-expert-witness/internet-expert-witness/">internet expert witness</a>, Dr. Lavian brings <a href="/about-dr-lavian/">academic and industrial research</a> experience and a Ph.D. from UC Berkeley, specializing in telecommunications, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-communications-expert-witness/">network communication</a>, and Internet technologies, to his consulting work.</p>

        <p>His expertise extends to <a href="/communications-expert-witness/mobile-wireless-expert/">computer networks</a>, data communications, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/internet-expert-witness/">LAN/WAN, TCP/IP, UDP, VPN</a>, VoIP, streaming media, chat, SMS, <a href="/us-10598764-radar-target-detection-and-imaging-system-for-autonomous-car/">mobile wireless</a>, Ethernet, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/routing-switching-expert/">routing</a>, switching, Internet, and web techs. Dr. Lavian offers expert witness services in patent cases, including expert testimony, expert witness reports, and patent analysis of Internet techs, standards, and protocols.</p>

        <p>Moreover, he offers expert witness services and provides courtroom presence, clear testimony, and the ability to quickly distill complex concepts into the basics.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has testified in Federal courts before judges and juries, the USPTO PTAB, and the ITC as a highly expert witness. He has supported Intellectual Property (IP) litigation cases related to over 140 patents in <a href="/us-20130080898-electronic-communications/">network communications</a> and telecommunications, including Internet Protocols (TCP/IP), streaming media, and mobile technologies. Cases involved leading companies such as Apple, Google, Microsoft, Samsung, Meta (Facebook), Amazon, Cisco Systems, AT&amp;T, Verizon, T-Mobile, Juniper Networks (HPE), Huawei, Arista, Motorola, LG, Avaya, and many others.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has experience working with law firms, giving expert witness services, patent analysis, prior art, source code reviews, hardware reviews, patent infringement, patent invalidity, trade secrets, and other related matters.</p>

        <p>Therefore, he has <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">testified as an expert witness</a> over 80 times in depositions and trials and has written numerous expert reports. These reports comprise state-of-the-art research and tech analysis regarding patent claims, invalidity/validity, infringement/non-infringement, claim constructions, and prior art.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian presents technical material in plain English common sense and uses terminology understandable by technical and lay audiences alike.</p>

        <div class="testimony-box">
          <h2>Expert testimony services and litigation support, including:</h2>

          <ul>
            <li>Dr. Lavian provides expert testimony and litigation support services, including:
              <ul>
                <li>Testifying as an expert in cases filed with the United States District Court, the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO), the International Trade Commission (ITC), and other courts in the United States, the Tax Court in Canada, and a court in Asia.</li>
                <li>Serving as an expert witness in USPTO PTAB proceedings, including Inter partes reviews (IPRs), Covered Business Method (CBM) reviews, Post Grant Reviews (PGRs), Ex-Parte Re-Examinations, and PTO Interferences.</li>
                <li>Providing technical education for claim constructions and Markman hearings.</li>
                <li>Writing expert reports, including analyses, claim term definitions, and claim construction.</li>
                <li>Communicating technical information effectively to audiences of varying levels of technical expertise.</li>
                <li>Providing product and technical analyses related to patent portfolios, claim charts, prior art investigation, and patentability research.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

